<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">BARDS FROM 12 TO 15 IN LFAY AREA</b></font> - <small>Monicrev of Bristlebane, BristleBain</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    One Word:  Bandits!<P><P>Now for the description....  At level 12, all most of the bandits are even or blue at the three bandit camp in Lesser Faydark.  The loc on the camp is 1350, 2000.  This is the approach from the south side of the camp.  Use the ever usefull level 8 Lull song and lull two of the bandits.  Use a ranged weapon and pull the third from the camp to the little hill.  Melee and mix in what spells you've learned.  I use different spells depending on what con the bandit is.  I have successfully soloed a yellow bandit here at level 11.  It was really close, but I outlasted him by 9 hit points.  I should warn you, that made me 1 for 13 on the yellows, so, at best, it's a terrible risk.<P><P>With the camp lulled, its basically a one on one fight.  If you have a bad lull and the entire camp comes, just Selo's to the zone line and go through.  Do not run to the ranger/druid station as the bandits are smart enough not to approach there.  Also, keep an eye out for Thistle and Whimsey.  Both wander through the area.  Thistle is 20+ (not quite sure, always red to me, hehehe) and Whimsy is a hard 15.<P><P>The best part of this camp is that the bandits drop bronze weapons.  The worst part is the six minute spawn time.  More times than not, at 13th and 14th level, I only fought the front two bandits.  They respawned before I was ready to pull the back bandit.<P><P>One other person makes this camp a lot easier, and gives you someone to talk to while you heal up.<P><P>The downside to this camp is that sometimes there is a waiting list to get in rotation.<P><P>I tried the Nybright Sisters camp, but with four sisters there, your lull on the first expires before you can successfully pull the unlulled one.  I have experimented with lulling the camp and pulling the one outside the camp, but my success rate was low doing it this way.<P><P>Cheers and may Bristlebane never take your voice!
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
